This repository contains two distinct pieces of code:

1. OCPQ (backend/, frontend/, tauri/, etc.), originally developed by
   Aaron Kuesters and available at https://github.com/aarkue/OCPQ.
   No license file was present in the original repository at the time
   this project was started; the code is included here for private,
   internal development while redistribution terms are being clarified
   directly with the original author.

2. The anonymity-framework extension (backend/shared/src/kanon/, the
   kanon-demo crate, and associated documentation), written for the
   companion in-preparation paper on k-anonymity in OCPQ. This part is
   covered by the MIT license in LICENSE.

This repository is currently private and not intended for public
redistribution until point 1 above is resolved.
